.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIcommand_file\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a lightweight UNIX command interpreter written in C that mimics the behavior of the standard shell.

It reads commands from the standard input or from a file and executes them.

.SH FEATURES
The shell supports:
.TP
\fBInteractive mode\fR
Displays a prompt and waits for user input.
.TP
\fBNon-interactive mode\fR
Executes commands passed from a pipe or a file.
.TP
\fBBuilt-in commands\fR
exit, env

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run interactively:
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) ls
main.c shell.c README.md
($) exit
.fi
.TP
Run non-interactively:
.nf
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
total 8
-rw-r--r-- 1 user user  200 Nov 12 14:32 main.c
-rwxr-xr-x 1 user user 4096 Nov 12 14:32 hsh
.fi

.SH RETURN VALUE
The exit status is that of the last command executed, or 0 if no command was run.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2), fork(2)

.SH AUTHORS
Abdullah Al-Asiri
